      "message": "Line 980: 🟡 If `getInterfaceAddr` with `pj_AF_INET()` fails and you fall through to `pj_AF_INET6()`, the subsequent `getInterfaceAddr` on line 984 could also fail, leaving `ifaceAddr` empty. The existing fallback on line 995-996 handles this, but adding a log when detection falls back to IPv6 would help with debugging:\n\n```suggestion\n    if (family \u003d\u003d pj_AF_UNSPEC()) {\n        auto addr4 \u003d dhtnet::ip_utils::getInterfaceAddr(account-\u003egetLocalInterface(), pj_AF_INET());\n        family \u003d addr4 ? pj_AF_INET() : pj_AF_INET6();\n        if (!addr4)\n            JAMI_DEBUG(\"No IPv4 address on interface, falling back to IPv6 for SDP offer\");\n    }\n```",
