      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 1552: 🟡 The comment says \u0027no NAT on IPv6\u0027, but this is an oversimplification. While IPv6 NAT (NAT66) is less common, it does exist in some enterprise and carrier-grade deployments. Consider weakening the comment to \u0027NAT is uncommon on IPv6\u0027 or \u0027STUN is typically not needed for IPv6\u0027. Additionally, if the transport is IPv6 but getLocalAddr returns a link-local address (fe80::), using it as the STUN result could cause reachability issues. Consider verifying that the returned address is a global unicast address.\n\n```suggestion\n    // Detect transport family - skip STUN for IPv6 (NAT is uncommon on IPv6,\n    // and pjstun_get_mapped_addr2 only supports IPv4)\n```",
